etymologies: late 19th century; earliest use found in The Century Dictionary. From scientific Latin Platycercus, genus name (from ancient Greek πλατύκερκος flat-tailed from πλατυ- + κέρκος tail) + -ine

definitions: Of, belonging to, or relating to a group of broad-tailed parrots typified by the genus Platycercus (now the subfamily Platycercinae), which includes the rosellas.
A parrot of the subfamily Platycercinae; a broad-tailed parrot.
